				<td rowspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" style="text-align: justify;" width="100%" valign=top>
				<DIV></DIV>
<P>Monday is here and it's been a long day.&nbsp; I think anyone who spends more then one full day at E3 probably wants to spend a few days in a dark quiet room, sensory overload is a bad thing mmmkay!!&nbsp; <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>&nbsp; So the show was awesome.&nbsp; Lots of great things to see which I am sure you know now just by checking out the various write ups out there...&nbsp; I know I was checking out G4 this morning to see what they had to say...</P>
<P>So really all I have are a bunch more pictures.&nbsp; I was able to get the others re-sized so they look much better now.&nbsp; The PC I was using in our booth must not like Halflings or something because it sure gave me a headache.</P>
<P>This is the front of our booth.&nbsp; This was basically the scene from Wednesday morning until Friday at 4.&nbsp; What a crowd!</P>
<P><IMG src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/images/forum_images/e3/Outside_booth.jpg"></P>
<P><BR>Here is a picture of your little Halfling Correspondent hard at work <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> Great magazine by the way!!</P>
<P><IMG src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/images/forum_images/e3/Ashlanne_SOE_Worlds.jpg"></P>
<P><BR>This is a great shot of our favorite Halfling, Brenlo.&nbsp; He is standing next to one of our great marketing folks.&nbsp; Some of you may remember her from the New Orleans Fan Faire Best of the Best Tournament.</P>
<P><IMG src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/images/forum_images/e3/Brenlo_Greenberg.jpg"><BR></P>
<P>Speaking of Fan Faire, here is a great shot of Fan Faire Jen!!&nbsp; Jen heads up the team that organizes Fan Faire.&nbsp; She and her team also organize events like E3, GenCom, and Comic Con...</P>
<P><IMG src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/images/forum_images/e3/fanfaireJen.jpg"></P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P><BR>Our booth always opens to SOE employees on Friday from 2 PM to 4 PM.&nbsp; You never know who might turn up.&nbsp; You folks know this guy...&nbsp; Here is EQ Designer Rahtiz...</P>
<P><IMG src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/images/forum_images/e3/Rahtiz_at_E3.jpg"></P>
<P><BR>I told you our booth was huge... This is a picture of part of the inside, you can see part of the smoothie machine behind that brick counter.&nbsp; <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-very-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></P>
<P><IMG src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/images/forum_images/e3/booth_inside.jpg"></P>
